@startuml
title Dynamic Scalability Architecture - Scaling Decision Logic

!include ../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/behavioral/activity-diagram-style.iuml

start
:Cloud service consumers send requests;
:Automated scaling listener monitors workload;

if (Predefined capacity threshold exceeded?) then (yes)
  :Evaluate scaling policy;
  if (Eligible for additional scaling?) then (yes)
    if (Type of dynamic scaling) is (horizontal) then
      :Signal resource replication;
      :Scale out / scale in instances;
    elseif (vertical) then
      :Adjust capacity of single resource;
      :Scale up / scale down\n(e.g., add RAM or core);
    else (relocation)
      :Relocate IT resource to host\nwith more capacity;
    endif
    :Resume monitoring;
  else (no)
    :Continue monitoring\n(no scaling action);
  endif
else (no)
  :Continue monitoring;
endif

stop

note right
  Mechanisms involved: automated scaling
  listener, resource replication, cloud
  usage monitor, hypervisor, pay-per-use
  monitor.
end note

@enduml
